        {
          "id": 60774,
          "name": "Additional Info",
          "text": "<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87); font-family: Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 300; letter-spacing: 0.16px;\">We need to expand the model of recommendations in action cards so that a single recommendation section can hold multiple recommendations with different conditions and scopes:</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87); font-family: Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 300; letter-spacing: 0.16px;\">Was is currently a 1:1 logic, means that a recommendation section has 1 text, 2 scope and 1 conditions ruke needs to be expanded into 1 1:n logic, like with questions inside an assessment section:</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87); font-family: Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 300; letter-spacing: 0.16px;\">Change logic that the section can hold multiple sub recommendations, each with the same logic as the current system.</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87); font-family: Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 300; letter-spacing: 0.16px;\">Benefit: We reduce the number of sections on a card. We already see cases where we show 2-3 section underneath each other and that can be confusing...</p>\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.87); font-family: Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 16px; font-weight: 300; letter-spacing: 0.16px;\">I would suggest to keep the current recommendation as \"first\" recommendation in place as it will be sufficient in many cases, but to add the ability to define \"sub\" recommendations as a list (like questions in an assessment). From a UI perspective, they show up as a list (if multiple are displayed) with the \"first\" being at the top.</p>\n<p><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: 'Segoe UI VSS (Regular)', 'Segoe UI', -apple-system, 'system-ui', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, Ubuntu, Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-weight: 400; letter-spacing: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial; display: inline !important; float: none;\">TBC: \"scopes\" or \"scores\"</span></p>",
          "tags": [{ "id": 3135, "name": "additional-nfo" }],
          "conditionRule": "OR",
          "isRecommendation": true,
          "scoreBased": 1,
          "maxScore": "0.00",
          "minScore": "1.00",
          "widgets": [],
          "setTags": []
        },
